properties.headline: Freeze Warning issued February 4 at 12:55AM PST until February 5 at 9:00AM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Sub-freezing temperatures generally between 27 and 31
degrees for the remainder of this morning and again tonight. The
coldest locations in the San Joaquin Valley will be affected by
sub-freezing temperatures as low as 25 degrees both this morning
and tonight. Sub-freezing temperatures are likely for a period
of six to eight hours both this morning and tonight.

* WHERE...San Joaquin Valley and Coastal Hills.

* WHEN...For the first Freeze Warning, until 9 AM PST this
morning. For the second Freeze Warning, from midnight tonight
to 9 AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Outdoor plumbing could be damaged. Sensitive, exposed
vegetation may die.
properties.instruction:
Bring pets indoors. Wrap outdoor plumbing to insulate pipes.
Cover sensitive, exposed vegetation to trap heat.
